<span id="freeTextContainer5164027874345736971">Firstly, I should to say I&apos;ve read &quot;Man search for meaning&quot; from Viktor Frankl who has been prisoner in the Auschwitz and this book which is called &quot;Death is my trade&quot; from Robert Merle about commander of the same prison. <br/>The author of this book wrote it by reading about Nazi officers confessions and investigation about their life. This book has retrieved from Rudolf Höss life. <br/>War in the word is that much dirty which I don&apos;t like to talk about it but I would like to talk about another side of t</span>
  <span id="freeText5164027874345736971" style="display:none">Firstly, I should to say I've read "Man search for meaning" from Viktor Frankl who has been prisoner in the Auschwitz and this book which is called "Death is my trade" from Robert Merle about commander of the same prison. <br />The author of this book wrote it by reading about Nazi officers confessions and investigation about their life. This book has retrieved from Rudolf Höss life. <br />War in the word is that much dirty which I don't like to talk about it but I would like to talk about another side of this real tragedy that results in killed about 1.5 million(I'm not sure about the number) human during 5 years. <br />He always claimed that on his confession I just did my duty and I did the commands. <br />But really we as human what would be our duty in return to others? <br />I like this part of book which is communication between Rudolf and American Colonel in the prison. Honestly what is the difference between Rudolf Höss and that Bomber Pilot who attacked Hiroshima and Nagasaki? <br />The answer is, that side who is winner won't be blame and there are a lot of example like this in history! <br />Victorious and Defeated, both of them should be blame because of their results which have been killed many people around the world who killed because of ridiculous belief of idiots leaders. These days we are witnessed many inhumanity, especially in the Middle East and it's the dirty politics!<br />At the end I should add I don't have problem with any nationality, I respect to any flag but we should accept it our leader's hands are bloody. We must not impact by their ridiculous slogan. Before everything find your own ideology and instead take a gun, increase your knowledge by education. <br />Hope one day love replace the extremism. </span>
