<div id="review_1744116876" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1744116876" />
    <a title="Michal Mironov" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48074717-michal-mironov"><img alt="Michal Mironov" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1455871962p2/48074717.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1744116876?book_show_action=true">Aug 31, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michal Mironov" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michal Mironov" href="/user/show/48074717-michal-mironov">Michal Mironov</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 8020607684" href="/book/show/7514029-smrt-je-m-m-emeslem">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1744116876" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4105103339896871277">A rather chilling “autobiography” of the former Auschwitz commander. Demonstration of how the institutionalized evil can become an integral part of every human being. The book is often written in a strict diary style - where human beings are mere numbers and mass murder is described as solving mathematical exercise. Höss (under the pseudonym Lange) acts as a pedant, honest and hard worker; however he completely lacks emotional intelligence. He doesn’t enjoy killing, just wants to be effective an</span>
  <span id="freeText4105103339896871277" style="display:none">A rather chilling “autobiography” of the former Auschwitz commander. Demonstration of how the institutionalized evil can become an integral part of every human being. The book is often written in a strict diary style - where human beings are mere numbers and mass murder is described as solving mathematical exercise. Höss (under the pseudonym Lange) acts as a pedant, honest and hard worker; however he completely lacks emotional intelligence. He doesn’t enjoy killing, just wants to be effective and useful. At some point, the reader almost sympathize with him (unlike Himmler, Lange took full responsibility for everything that happened in Auschwitz). The author skilfully exploited his wide knowledge about the Holocaust and connected it with the knowledge of psychology. A powerful book, tough reading...</span>
  <a data-text-id="4105103339896871277" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


