<div id="review_132051680" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/132051680" />
    <a title="Sadie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3057525-sadie"><img alt="Sadie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1557910132p2/3057525.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/132051680?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sadie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sadie" href="/user/show/3057525-sadie">Sadie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9783746612126" href="/book/show/157557.Der_Tod_ist_mein_Beruf">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=ty-fiction">ty-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-in-2010">read-in-2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=medium-book">medium-book</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=g-historical-fiction">g-historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-in-german">read-in-german</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=read-author-male-only">read-author-male-only</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3057525-sadie?shelf=3-stars-liked">3-stars-liked</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer132051680" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9812071343404771470">This took me quite a while to finish. One reason was the style I never could really got into - which is a shame, since this is a really good book, good in the way the (true) horror grabs you and makes you wonder/shake your head at the &quot;how&quot; and &quot;why&quot;. This is the (semi/somewhat) fictional biographical story about Rudolf Lang, who would be Rudolf Hoeß, the commander of Auschwitz concentration camp. The horror is real/has been real, and, needless to say, Lang/Hoeß is a messed up a character as it </span>
  <span id="freeText9812071343404771470" style="display:none">This took me quite a while to finish. One reason was the style I never could really got into - which is a shame, since this is a really good book, good in the way the (true) horror grabs you and makes you wonder/shake your head at the "how" and "why". This is the (semi/somewhat) fictional biographical story about Rudolf Lang, who would be Rudolf Hoeß, the commander of Auschwitz concentration camp. The horror is real/has been real, and, needless to say, Lang/Hoeß is a messed up a character as it gets. Gruesome, painful, very much so.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9812071343404771470" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


