<span id="freeTextContainer17782560787937729938">I read a lot of books about the holocaust, world war 2, and Germany who played an important role in them. This book was different from others. it was a fictionalized biographical novel by Robert Merle. The protagonist, Rudolf Lang, was closely based on the real Rudolf Hoß, commandant of the concentration camp Auschwitz. I think the author combined the history of the holocaust and psychological problems for the commandant of the concentration camp Auschwitz. by reading this book you can understan</span>
  <span id="freeText17782560787937729938" style="display:none">I read a lot of books about the holocaust, world war 2, and Germany who played an important role in them. This book was different from others. it was a fictionalized biographical novel by Robert Merle. The protagonist, Rudolf Lang, was closely based on the real Rudolf Hoß, commandant of the concentration camp Auschwitz. I think the author combined the history of the holocaust and psychological problems for the commandant of the concentration camp Auschwitz. by reading this book you can understand what happened to a person gradually to change him into an emotionless monster.<br />on his confession, he always claimed that I just did my duties and I did the commands and it is not my fault. I think several people will say this because just they want to do their duties and they do not think about the results and consequences that their works will have! <br /> <br />But I like this question in the book: What is the difference between Rudolf Höss and that Bomber Pilot who attacked Hiroshima and Nagasaki?<br />In my idea victorious and Defeated, both of them should be blamed because of their results they war and kill a lot of people only because of the ridiculous belief of idiots leaders!</span>
