<div id="review_4326672218" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4326672218" />
    <a title="Neringa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32500549-neringa"><img alt="Neringa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1635703874p2/32500549.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4326672218?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Neringa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Neringa" href="/user/show/32500549-neringa">Neringa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4326672218" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13145788049556755168">Such a dark book based on real memoirs of the protagonist. Tells the story of a german boy and his story of becoming an SS officer, precisely - the commandant of Auschwitz. The worst (or maybe best) aspect of this book is that it is so difficult to truly see the monstruous nature of Rudolph Lang (aka Rudolf Höss in real life). He was just following orders... Didn&apos;t even accept his part in the murder of hundreds of thousands of Jews. *I was just following orders* - he says. <br/>And the scariest part </span>
  <span id="freeText13145788049556755168" style="display:none">Such a dark book based on real memoirs of the protagonist. Tells the story of a german boy and his story of becoming an SS officer, precisely - the commandant of Auschwitz. The worst (or maybe best) aspect of this book is that it is so difficult to truly see the monstruous nature of Rudolph Lang (aka Rudolf Höss in real life). He was just following orders... Didn't even accept his part in the murder of hundreds of thousands of Jews. *I was just following orders* - he says. <br />And the scariest part of this is that we keep doing that even today. Just like Rudolph, we place orders over our own conscience. But it is us and always us who take action... I guess for me that was the most important message of this book - you can do everything perfectly according to the standards required from you and ... be a monster. <br />Highly recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13145788049556755168" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
