<div id="review_3649345933" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3649345933" />
    <a title="Gabriela" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/124620547-gabriela"><img alt="Gabriela" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3649345933?book_show_action=true">Aug 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabriela" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabriela" href="/user/show/124620547-gabriela">Gabriela</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3649345933" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10306117836925040921">Superbly written book about a man with dull personality, zero emotional intelligence who, if he wasn&apos;t given orders to follow, would probably implode. Completely incapable of judging the morality of his actions, people like him are the reason idiots like Hitler got to rise to power. Shows how people (although he acts more like a machine, really) like him, once they&apos;re told a lie believe it and see evidence for it where there&apos;s none. It&apos;s truly a masterpiece of a book, made me feel a pit in my st</span>
  <span id="freeText10306117836925040921" style="display:none">Superbly written book about a man with dull personality, zero emotional intelligence who, if he wasn't given orders to follow, would probably implode. Completely incapable of judging the morality of his actions, people like him are the reason idiots like Hitler got to rise to power. Shows how people (although he acts more like a machine, really) like him, once they're told a lie believe it and see evidence for it where there's none. It's truly a masterpiece of a book, made me feel a pit in my stomach while reading certain sections but especially the ending. Very important book about brainwashing, complete and utter apathy and it's dire consequences. Tough read but an important one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10306117836925040921" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
